    "EchoCLIP represents an opportunity to automate many of individual patients by cosine similarity (n = 2,959).",
    "Each line represents an individual patient with time from major clinical event on the x axis and cosine similarity versus first study on the y axis.",
    "Patients either had major cardiac surgery (c) or heart transplant (d), with cosine similarity calculated at the study level and pairwise compared for all videos in each study.",
    "Data are from the Cedars-Sinai Medical Center.",
    "FPR, false positive rate; TPR, true positive rate."
